      • cleanCaches

        protected void cleanCaches(boolean indDelete)
        Description copied from class: SimpleNode
        Called when underlying MutableConfig data have changed so that any cache that could contain instantiated objects whose states are dependent on this data is cleared. The current SimpleNode and its children are traversed and the same method is called on all of them because of the inheritance mechanisms implemented in Dragom.

        Subclasses that manage such caches must override which method to add the appropriate behavior.

        Overrides:
        cleanCaches in class SimpleNode
        Parameters:
        indDelete - Indicates to perform a full clean and put the MutableNode in the State.DELETED to make it unusable.
